# Accepted risks — each one is a deliberate cost/benefit call for a public
# demo portfolio with a hard "idle ≈ $0" budget rule (see CLAUDE.md).
# Revisit if any plank starts handling real (non-demo) data.

# CloudFront without WAF: a web ACL costs ~$5+/mo per distribution. The sites
# are static pages behind OAC with strict security headers; the APIs enforce
# auth + per-user/global rate caps at the application layer.
AVD-AWS-0011

# S3 with SSE-S3 (AES256) instead of a customer-managed KMS key: CMKs cost
# $1/mo each + per-request. Nothing in these buckets is sensitive: public
# site assets, a fictional demo corpus, terraform state (whose bucket is
# created outside terraform with encryption + versioning + public-block).
AVD-AWS-0132

# Unencrypted SNS topics: they carry CloudWatch alarm notifications and
# plank 3's fictional service-request fan-out (no payload secrets).
# Encrypting would require a CMK ($1/mo) because neither CloudWatch nor
# EventBridge can publish through the AWS-managed aws/sns key.
AVD-AWS-0095
